{"abstract": "We present the Hourglass Diffusion Transformer (HDiT), an image generative model that exhibits linear scaling with pixel count, supporting training at high-resolution (e.g. $1024 \\times 1024$) directly in pixel-space. Building on the Transformer architecture, which is known to scale to billions of parameters, it bridges the gap between the efficiency of convolutional U-Nets and the scalability of Transformers. HDiT trains successfully without typical high-resolution training techniques such as multiscale architectures, latent autoencoders or self-conditioning. We demonstrate that HDiT performs competitively with existing models on ImageNet $256^2$, and sets a new state-of-the-art for diffusion models on FFHQ-$1024^2$.", "referenced_work_ids": ["527bc1af6f644a49f503d63a7d8c188665229400", "8fafd95a6ffbecf9c1b5f4542ac4b78a00602551", "e04da3c945aae8e2211222d373e7bf771d6412a7", "8c42e56ebc1328c55d4e7641adcdb3d85fed22c3", "f5a0c57f90c6abe31482e9f320ccac5ee789b135", "ca21f28e2a0a8205038301d8385151ab7ca2a050", "d37ee0c440e36df133722093f6a824f4964e8ae0", "eaa3a21fe70d7c2e4de3c92274daa4a8eca7b277", "57e849d0de13ed5f91d086936296721d4ff75a75", "61e721334296ebfbbf6443b5ed9eb8c83b708c95", "6e3a3b7a8a0376d867cad72eedf2f9b746f29a33", "736973165f98105fec3729b7db414ae4d80fcbeb", "3d3a76a2fedccea741f34303b06358440dc2a212", "897f3bb5eacaa80359e81ff33378e1110e20ae95", "a815b0a955db2163617baf308020c3d770da099d", "af9f365ed86614c800f082bd8eb14be76072ad16", "2f4c451922e227cbbd4f090b74298445bbd900d0", "9695824d7a01fad57ba9c01d7d76a519d78d65e7", "a26a7a74f1e5fd562be95c3611a0680759fbdf84", "82ba96443173da0b8b3e870c5ab8f41109a67203", "c10075b3746a9f3dd5811970e93c8ca3ad39b39d", "5553f9508dd1056ecc20c5b1f367e9a07e2c7e81", "be0fbb810583930c071d0b9b2c5187fe260783f5", "231e768f0cd280faa0f725bb353262cb4fed08d1", "eaf3a64b637b3699678374a2afe8dde05d17a5cc", "2835951fabf12804e17d5a525b2be2bee70e7910", "0f183bcfe65781c06b1a48a6f56e0f3c63e8e4a4", "64ea8f180d0682e6c18d1eb688afdb2027c02794",